{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f5b722df-77d0-4d5f-9cf0-ea8bf89f1d24",
    "name": "Logistics & Shipment Tracking System API",
    "description": "=== WHO TO USE FOR WHAT ===\n\n🔵 ADMIN TOKEN → Folder 2 (Admin Actions), Folder 7 (Metrics/Dashboard), Admin Disputes\n   Real user: admin@example.com | DB id: 64ac5abd-ecef-4092-958a-17f30dc5f66b\n   Switch: set access_token = {{admin_token}}\n\n🟢 CUSTOMER TOKEN → Folder 4 (Shipment Booking), Folder 6 (Raise Dispute), Folder 9 (Notifications)\n   Real user: arjun.customer@example.com | DB id: 9340ef1a-7063-43cf-a9af-2bddf4df6a0a\n   Switch: set access_token = {{customer_token}}\n\n🟡 DRIVER TOKEN → Folder 3 (Driver Setup), Folder 5 (Claims & Delivery Flow)\n   Real user: ravi.driver@example.com | DB id: 94f53dd1-a079-44d4-96d3-7a9a97553e02\n   Switch: set access_token = {{driver_token}}\n\n⚪ NO TOKEN → Folder 8 (Public Tracking) — no auth needed\n\n🗄️ FAKE DATA (seed script) → Used for visual demo only. These users have no tokens.\n   Fake drivers (pending approval): Muthu Kumar, Selvam Raja\n   Fake shipments: Various statuses visible in admin dashboard\n   Fake disputes: Pre-seeded for admin to resolve\n\n=== DEMO FLOW ORDER ===\n1. Admin: Get Pending Drivers → Approve one → Reject one\n2. Driver: Add Vehicle → Set Active → Go Online\n3. Customer: Create Shipment (COD) → note the shipmentId and senderOtp\n4. Driver: Get Available Jobs → Claim Job\n5. Driver: Confirm Pickup (enter senderOtp from step 3)\n6. Driver: Send GPS Pings (x3)\n7. Customer/Admin: Get Live Coordinates\n8. Driver: Confirm Delivery (enter receiverOtp from public track)\n9. Driver: Confirm Cash Collected\n10. Public: Track Order (no token)\n11. Customer: Raise Dispute\n12. Admin: List Disputes → Resolve Dispute",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Get Tokens (Auth0)",
      "description": "Run each request once to get tokens. Copy access_token from response into the matching variable (customer_token, driver_token, admin_token).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Customer Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('customer_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('Customer token saved');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"client_id\": \"{{client_id}}\",\n  \"client_secret\": \"{{client_secret}}\",\n  \"audience\": \"{{audience}}\",\n  \"grant_type\": \"password\",\n  \"username\": \"arjun.customer@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"{{user_password}}\",\n  \"scope\": \"openid profile email\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://{{auth0_domain}}/oauth/token",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["{{auth0_domain}}"],
              "path": ["oauth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Auto-saves token to customer_token and sets access_token to customer. Run this before testing customer endpoints."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Driver Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('Driver token saved');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"client_id\": \"{{client_id}}\",\n  \"client_secret\": \"{{client_secret}}\",\n  \"audience\": \"{{audience}}\",\n  \"grant_type\": \"password\",\n  \"username\": \"ravi.driver@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"{{user_password}}\",\n  \"scope\": \"openid profile email\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://{{auth0_domain}}/oauth/token",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["{{auth0_domain}}"],
              "path": ["oauth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Auto-saves token to driver_token and switches access_token to driver. Run before driver endpoint tests."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Admin Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('Admin token saved');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"client_id\": \"{{client_id}}\",\n  \"client_secret\": \"{{client_secret}}\",\n  \"audience\": \"{{audience}}\",\n  \"grant_type\": \"password\",\n  \"username\": \"admin@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"{{user_password}}\",\n  \"scope\": \"openid profile email\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://{{auth0_domain}}/oauth/token",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["{{auth0_domain}}"],
              "path": ["oauth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Auto-saves token to admin_token and switches access_token to admin. Run before admin endpoint tests."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "→ Switch to Customer Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', pm.collectionVariables.get('customer_token'));",
                  "console.log('Switched to CUSTOMER token');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/shipments?page=1&pageSize=1", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","shipments"], "query": [{"key":"page","value":"1"},{"key":"pageSize","value":"1"}] },
            "description": "Run this to switch active token to CUSTOMER before customer API calls. Just a helper — ignore the response."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "→ Switch to Driver Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', pm.collectionVariables.get('driver_token'));",
                  "console.log('Switched to DRIVER token');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/shipments/available", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","shipments","available"] },
            "description": "Run this to switch active token to DRIVER before driver API calls."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "→ Switch to Admin Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', pm.collectionVariables.get('admin_token'));",
                  "console.log('Switched to ADMIN token');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/metrics", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","admin","metrics"] },
            "description": "Run this to switch active token to ADMIN before admin API calls."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
